(
 '<h3>Admin commands</h3>'
 '<ul><li>Send message with "⍙cmd_subscribe⍙ {email}" to the list to subscribe user with given email. They will be asked for confirmation.</li>'
 '<li>Send message with "⍙cmd_unsubscribe⍙ {email}" to the list to immediately unsubscribe user with given email.</li>'
 '<li>Send message with "⍙cmd_listmembers⍙" to the list to receive a member list with email address, status and join date.</li>'
 '<li>Send message with "⍙cmd_log⍙ [n] [filter]" to the list to receive recent log entries. The optional filter matches exactly on log level (ERR, WARN, INFO, DBG), category (SYS, SUB, ADM, SMTP, BOUNCE, SEC), or as a free-text substring. Examples: "⍙cmd_log⍙" (last 100 lines), "⍙cmd_log⍙ 200" (last 200 lines), "⍙cmd_log⍙ ERR" (errors only), "⍙cmd_log⍙ 50 SYS" (last 50 lines filtered to SYS), "⍙cmd_log⍙ BOUNCE" (bounce events only).</li>'
 '<li>Send message with "⍙cmd_setcfg⍙" and a JSON object in the body to change configuration settings. Editable fields: log_level (0=ERR 1=WARN 2=INFO 3=DBG), log_console (0/1), ratelimit_window_secs, ratelimit_max, confirm_window_hours, attachments (0/1), attachments_maxbytes, list_name, readonly (0/1), privacy_url, welcome_url (http/https URL to an HTML welcome page), welcome_include_help (0/1; append standard help after welcome content). Example body: {"welcome_url": "https://example.org/welcome.html", "welcome_include_help": 1}. Changes take effect immediately and persist across restarts.</li>'
 '<li>Send message with "⍙cmd_restart⍙" to restart the Alisia process.</li></ul>'
)
